  <description><![CDATA[<p style="margin: 0px 0px 11px;">Villasanpaolo Spa Hotel has an almost perfect spot in Tuscany. It’s surrounded by countryside and close to San Gimignano so your views from the pool will be olive groves, vineyards and San Gimignano’s Medieval towers in the background. We can’t think of anywhere better to relax for the day. Except maybe the hotel’s spa, which is over 1,000 square metres. The indoor hydro-massage pool is idyllic and it connects outside so you relax in the gardens too. With Inghams you'll have three hours free use of the facilities included in the price of your holiday. If you'd like more time in the spa or to book a massage or treatment, you can for a local fee. </p>
<p style="margin: 0px 0px 11px;">This is a really nice base for exploring Tuscany. The rooms are very welcoming and have a typical Tuscan style. With San Gimignano just two miles away, it’s easy to jump in your car and explore. This is the middle of the Chianti region so wine tasting is an absolute must! You can carry on the tastings in the evenings at the hotel’s restaurant. There’s plenty of labels to choose from on the wine list. The food is worth shouting about too. They use local product, including olive oil made in their grounds. Everything is delicious here – we’re still dreaming about the ricotta cheesecake we had a few years back.</p>
<p style="margin: 0px 0px 11px;">Car hire is recommended for this hotel. Villasanpaolo Spa Hotel is approx. 1 hour 10 mins from Pisa airport.</p>]]></description>
